-- Cargill Says Second-Quarter Earnings Quadruple to $409 Million
-- B y   S h r u t i   D a t e   S i n g h
-- 2013-01-09T14:11:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-09/cargill-says-second-quarter-earnings-quadruple-to-409-million.html
Cargill Inc., the largest closely
held U.S. company, said fiscal second-quarter profit quadrupled
with earnings improving at four of its five business segments.  Net income climbed to $409 million in the three months
through November from $100 million a year earlier, the
Minneapolis-based company said today in a statement. Sales rose
6 percent to $35.2 billion.  To contact the reporter on this story:
